# Placeholder for the v2 FRP migration.
#
# When you're ready to swap Cloudflare Tunnel for self-hosted FRP, this is
# where the VPS-side Caddyfile goes. Rename this to `Caddyfile` and deploy it
# to the VPS that hosts your frps.
#
# The architecture then looks like:
#
#   [client]
#       ↓ HTTPS
#   [llm.yourdomain.com] → [your VPS]
#                            Caddy (terminates TLS, Let's Encrypt)
#                              ↓ HTTP
#                            frps (listens on 7000)
#                              ↑ reverse tunnel
#                            frpc (runs in the SkyPilot container)
#                              ↓
#                            llama-server :8080
#
# Clients keep pointing at https://llm.yourdomain.com/v1 — the URL does not
# change between v1 (CF Tunnel) and v2 (FRP). Only the DNS target changes:
# CNAME to the CF tunnel → A-record to this VPS's IP.
#
# See README.md §"Migrating to FRP" for the full swap procedure.
#
# Example Caddyfile for the VPS (uncomment and customize when migrating):
#
# llm.yourdomain.com {
#     reverse_proxy localhost:8080
# }
#
# Where localhost:8080 is what frps exposes locally after accepting the
# reverse tunnel from frpc running inside the SkyPilot container.
